TextBody:
Gary,
Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support. 

What software is currently installed?
Could we get the text output (copy&past) from the following ADMIN PowerShell ISE script block on the systems that are running Netwrix/Stealth Server applications?

Clear-Host  # Clears the console window for better readability. 
#Netwrix/Stealth, PostgreSQL, Python application versions:
Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Product |
Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "*Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue |
Sort-Object | Format-Table Name,Version,InstallDate -AutoSize 

#Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) install path
$env:SAINSTALLDIR 

#Netwrix Access Information Center (AIC) formally StealthAUDIT Access Information Center (AIC) install path
(Get-ItemProperty -Path "HKLM:SYSTEMCurrentControlSetServicesAccessInformationCenter"-ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).ImagePath.Replace("`"", "").Replace("BinAccessInformationCenter.Service.exe", "")


For this 45min Prep meeting, we will need to have a Full Admin access to the following
Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) Server.

Hi Dusty,

I worked with our DBA after the call, we verified that the account we used had DBA to all the Netwrix DB's.  When I went into settings to validate the DB config and select the DB, we got the error:

[cid:image001.png@01DBADD3.06FCD820]

I clicked OK and then clicked Apply, it appeared to work based on these results.
[cid:image002.png@01DBADD3.621A7F50]

I closed and saved the config and then ran the create schema job, but it still failed - it ran up to around 120 of 132 tasks in the 1. Create Tables analysis job and failed and also failed the Data Migration Task.

Our DBA then gave me SA rights so I went in and ran the same steps.  This time I did not get the error selecting the DB, but got the below option.  I selected the default and click OK.
[cid:image003.png@01DBADD4.B530AE20]

It finished the transfer, so I click Finish.
[cid:image004.png@01DBADD4.B530AE20]


I then got the errors below as I click through the OK's.
[cid:image005.png@01DBADD5.1EA0DE20]
[cid:image006.png@01DBADD5.1EA0DE20]
[cid:image007.png@01DBADD5.1EA0DE20]

I ran the schema job and again failed with the same errors.

We looked in the DB tables, but we did not see the SA_FSAA_AzureFilesShares.ResourceID table that was being referenced in the error.  I have also attached the log from the job.

Thanks,
Gary

SELECT

            ,suser_sname(sid) AS 'Owner ID'
